                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_109232">Cold-Ashby</placeName>.

   <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename>, prior of <orgName role="prior" key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </orgName>
                        </persName>, leases to <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> abbot of <orgName role="abbot" key="org_108033">Pipewell</orgName> the rectory of <placeName key="place_109232">Coldeashby</placeName>
                        </persName> for 90 years at £8 a year. On the death of the present vicar, <persName>Sir <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Simond</surname>
                        </persName>, they shall also have the vicarage for a further £10 a year. <orgName key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </orgName> may distrain for either of these rents, and if they are not paid within 10 weeks of the due time D<supplied>aventry</supplied> shall receive a fine of 20/-. For every Sunday on which the prior and convent of D<supplied>aventry</supplied> are not ’rehersed and praied for’ in the Church, they shall receive a fine of 12d. 
    
   <origDate when="1492-03-20">20 March 1492.</origDate>
                     </p>
